-- O’Brien Sought Independent News African Disposals, Post Reports
-- B y   J o e   B r e n n a n
-- 2012-06-03T11:05:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-03/o-brien-sought-independent-news-african-disposals-post-reports.html
Independent News & Media Plc (INM) ’s
largest shareholder,  Denis O’Brien , told the media company it
should sell its  South African interests  and invest the proceeds
in its  Australian and Asian businesses , the  Sunday Business Post 
reported, citing documents from board meetings.  O’Brien, who owns 29.9 percent of Independent News, made
the proposal to the Dublin-based company’s former Chairman Brian Hillery in August, the newspaper said.  James Morrissey, a spokesman for O’Brien, and Pat Walsh, a
spokesman for Independent News, declined to comment when
contacted by Bloomberg News today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joe Brennan in Dublin at 
